Package biz.sudden.baseAndUtility.domain.connectable

Interface Summary
Connectable Connectable represents a marker interface for classes which can be associated via AssociationRole and Association respectively Note: if you write a class which implements Connectable, extend package-info.java (in biz.sudden directory) -> the extension is needed to ensure accurate functionality for associating Connectables.
Value<T> Value is a generic Interface for concrete Occurrence values
 

Class Summary
Association Association - Associations represent relationships between Connectables.
AssociationRole AssociationRole - AssociationRoles provide the link between Connectables and Associations.
AssocRoleType AssocRoleType - AssocRoleTypes represent the nature of AssociationRoles.
AssocType AssocType - AssocTypes represent the nature of Associations.
BaseConnectable  
MethodCallValue The Value is actually a reference to some method call result using java -reflection.
Occurrence Occurrences are a Connectable's links to the 'outer world'.
OccurType OccurType defines the type of an occurrence.
Scope Scope defines the valid context of Statements [Associations, Occurrences].
Statement Statements are currently Associations and Occurrences.
StringValue StringValue represents a concrete value type for Occurrences
